HEADWORD: Unbonnet
<hw>Un*bon"net</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>bonnet</ets>.]</ety> <def>To take a bonnet from;
to take off one's bonnet; to uncover; <as>as, to <ex>unbonnet</ex> one's
head</as>.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

